  "headerNotes": [],
  "steps": [
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Identifying Antarctica",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "centeredImage",
          "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/0_aq_summary.png"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_snow.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/WdvUjKikrvCAbKnTA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Most of Antarctica is covered in **snow and ice**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_darksoil.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/rX871TMMebN15wqg9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The soil will always be **dark**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_pingwings.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/aAvFMEQ8jfkek3M88",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "**Penguins** can be found on parts of the coverage.",
              "NOTE: This is mostly useful to exclude coverage in the Arctics."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Regional clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_halfmoonisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/FSAzovZcXiTLsyHL6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Half Moon Island was covered by a **tripod**. It can also be recognized by the numerous other people in red jackets."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_deceptionisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/Gj7cPhS9x5U15ugp6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The **Deception Island Bay** can be recognized by the blue and white ship in the bay, and the abandoned equipment on the beach."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_deceptionislandconga.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/swvB96kQYetBxFwy8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The trekker can be seen **walking in a line **on Deception Island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_deceptionislanddarkbeach.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/sqvn11NCvto2voh6A",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "A beach with **black sand** and many penguins can be seen on Deception Island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_cuvervilleisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/MM4jjEUWScfLfeaRA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Cuverville Island can be recognised by the overcast weather combined with the coastline to the **northwest**. You\u2019ll also see a decent number of penguins, particularly [toward the east](https://goo.gl/maps/EVEBMqPQCrBaeptV6)."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_dancoisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/gBuhotZS2bQfrf3K7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Danco Island can be recognised by the **beautiful sunset coverage** over a snowy fjord."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_petermannisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/WUnCLoJWf27e4EUv8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Petermann Island can be recognized by the layer of snow with patches of **exposed rocks**, and the overexposed camera."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_rossisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/q1ELtwJAtkANiymK8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The coverage at the western tip of Ross Island can typically be recognised by the extremely dark, and mostly barren, **rocky soil**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_rossislandcabin.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/uPXAtuGAxSUEUy9k6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "A tripod featuring the exterior and [interior](https://goo.gl/maps/s9oJFd4Q8Vuretn89) of a small wooden cabin with a **grey metal roof **can be found south of the eastern tip of Ross Island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_mcmurdo.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/v1NYrq3KVTwiQoSH6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "McMurdo Station is the largest research station on Antarctica, and can be recognized by the **dark brown soil**, **many buildings**, American infrastructure and sunset coverage.",
              "NOTE: A lot of the coverage around McMurdo Station has the sun setting in the south, which shouldn\u2019t lead you to guess in the northern hemisphere."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_mcmurdotripods.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/HcARGup685XbAc4FA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "You can also find tripod coverage inside [several](https://goo.gl/maps/Pa8CQWgr7CmcTBvt7) [buildings](https://goo.gl/maps/JLbjTgt5ibVGp7SF8) at McMurdo Station."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_mcmurdohut.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/NizvjKX7WiCXrc2VA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "On the eastern side of McMurdo Station you can find a small wooden cabin, having a [tripod going inside](https://goo.gl/maps/LfHyR3gHdYmXM7TBA)."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_icetrekker.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/hTguZarvbp4eNazB7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Southeast of McMurdo station, the trekker can be seen walking on a layer of ice around **various machinery**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_mainlandvalleys.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/p1n1tgcGbNEa3J5fA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The trekker can be seen walking through a fantastical landscape consisting of many **desolate valleys** on mainland Antarctica, west of Ross Island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_blackisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/3w5rtf8c1hvmRAZo9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "A **vast, snowy landscape **with spread out hills can be seen south of McMurdo station."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_southpole.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/bPnDUuJDiiSAtmoY6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The tripod at the **south pole** can be recognized by numerous countries\u2019 flags around the tripod, and a sign with \u2018Geographic South Pole\u2019 written on it.",
              "This location is often on community-made world maps for a better scoring range."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/antarctica/aq_southpoleobservatory.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/tubFheZLxov1FxXz9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The South Pole Observatory has tripod coverage going around and inside of it."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "draftChangelog": []
}